
Overview of adj melodramatic

The adj melodramatic has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                    
1. (1) melodramatic -- (having the excitement and emotional appeal of melodrama; "a melodramatic account of two perilous days at sea")
2. histrionic, melodramatic -- (characteristic of acting or a stage performance; often affected; "histrionic gestures"; "an attitude of melodramatic despair"; "a theatrical pose")
